{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d2378081-d212-4cdd-91e1-a9d5dccaa75f","content":"On macOS, when a NativeAOT app crashes, look in these locations:\n\n1. **Apple Crash Reports** — macOS automatically generates `.ips` crash reports:\n   ```\n   ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n   Files are named like `YourApp_YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS_machinename.ips`.\n\n2. **Console.app** — Open Console → \"Crash Reports\" in the sidebar to browse them interactively.\n\n3. **Core dumps** (if enabled):\n   ```bash\n   ulimit -c unlimited   # enable before running\n   ```\n   Core files land in `/cores/core.<pid>`.\n\nThe `.ips` crash report includes the faulting thread, stack trace, and signal info — usually enough to start debugging without a full core dump.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7a914260-dae8-465d-bcdb-74809fb1b9df","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT app on macOS when `createdump` isn't available. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":271,"requestId":"AC0F:13323C:14B3FBC:1722560:6A06712A"},"id":"7417cdf9-5c1b-41e9-bf39-3ecfa42124fb","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:04:50.396Z","parentId":"e207e2bd-b712-4629-8233-8fa7aad7a896"}
